caption: I love it here!!  The food, the ambience and the staff are top notch!!!!  But what I love the most is that the staff as well as management are opened to suggestions.  My type of settings.

The baby backs and beef ribs are excellent. Friendly efficient service. Right by GW Bridge so slow down at Ft Lee Exit or will miss the turn off and cheap gas refill before crossing to NY.  They deliver locally.
Amazing food. Great service
Everything is simply awesome. Wait... Only if you like smoked food and only if you are not vegeterian.

Tried this place for the first time. Drinks we good! my husband got an LIT and I went with an old fashioned. Atmosphere is cute also it's very welcoming. However the food was just average. The brisket was a bit too salty as well as the pulled pork and wings. The mac and cheese unfortunately tasted like it came from a box but the beans were tasty.

Hands down the best BBQ place around! Their beef brisket is just perfect!! Quarter chicken always tender & moist inside, and baby back ribs & pulled pork all have the best barbecue flavors and spices.
Great service.
Loved it. Ribs and the corn bread are off the charts!!!
One of the best beef rib burgers I have ever had!
I ordered the brisket and the rib, which was tasty but I'm only giving it 3 stars because I was disappointed with the portion size of their rib. For $14, you get 1 rib. What is that?
Went for the first time yesterday with friends and everything was amazing - highly suggest the pull pork - definitely going back for more!!!
Like no other place
We ordered OISO takeout 2 weeks in a row and their bbq is well down and delicious. I was a bit let down by their seafood boil for its size. However, the flavor was on point.
Baby back ribs are delicious
(Translated by Google) It's so delicious that I want to go every day~  (Original) 넘흐 맛있어서 맨날 가고 싶어요~

My husband and I discovered this place recently and we have been coming here since then. My favorite on their menu is a brisket burger, but everything else is so delicious. The service is excellent, waiters are very friendly. Food is also served fast.
THE BEST BBQ IVE EVER HAD. Period. Amazing bacon, ribs and the chicken wings were amazing!!! You will not be disappointed
The food is MAGNIFICENT!  Ordered a wide array of items on the menu to sample. Absolutely phenomenal!!!
Love the food and service it became my favorite place
Oiso was delicious!!! We couldn't decide, so we got a little bit of everything (land) and everything was delicious!! Will go back soon and will recommend to everyone!

I have ordered food here twice.  The first time was shortly after they opened.  The bbq was average, and I feel under smoked and over sauced to cover the lack of smoking time.  But I gave it another try a few weeks later and was pleasantly surprised.  The smoke time was better, and the sauce was not longer overpowering.  I realize now that maybe they were not at 100% when they first opened.
Delicious brisket!
Great services, lots off food average price incredible drinks.
Great dinner here! Baby back ribs, and try the bacon too! Cornbread and fries - excellent.

Their cornbread is literally the best. Idk why but the cornbread is just stuck in my head and honesty wanna just order like 10 of them. Combo trays are really nice. Dont have to go all the way to New York for good texas bbq anymore🧡

Servers are very kind and all food is so delicious ❤️ they have many alcohol beverages! I ordered boiling pot, beef rib and some sides and that’s enough for two ppl. Outside dining is cozy and they’re enough social distances between tables. There’s enough parking space too!
(Translated by Google) First of all, the meat is so soft.. I ate it well because he gave me a lot of service!!  (Original) 일단 고기가 너무 부드러움.. 서비스도 많이주셔서 넘 잘먹었어요!!

One of my goto spots.  Some of the best BBQ I have ever had!   Great service and pleasant, comfortable atmosphere.  Prices and very reasonable for excellent quality and a quantity. Definitely a place to visit.
You should definitely try beef rib!

Food extremely tasteful. I had the mixed brisket and my friend had the seasoned fries. We shared both. Scene and great care by servers and others as they cleaned tables before we sat. Expect right-size portions for the price. In other words value was probably 4.5, but for the area and taste, establishment deserved the 5 star
Welcome to Fort Lee! Glad to have such an amazing taste and vibe here!
Very new but attractive vibe that makes me want to come back again. Enjoyed their boiling pot so much. Their mac & cheese was good too.
Casual place with amazing food!! Baked oysters, brisket, ribs, and haban corn - AH-MAZING!!
Delicious steak, great atmosphere, friendly staff, outdoor dining available

The ribs took a bit of time but the owner made up with serving some beef briskets on the house and it was by far the best meat I've tasted. Their sides are also very authentic and the baby back ribs are a must. Lucky to have this place right next to my apartment, and will visit again for sure.
Very friendly server. Mediocre at best BBQ.

Combo Tray B is value menu !
Highly recommend the beef ribs! Tender, juicy and tasty! Quarter chicken was a little dry though...
Delicious food.
I tried their all burgers. Very unique, and very outstanding! French fries were ok, coleslaw was very comforting, and cucumber pickle was awesome. Highly recommended!
Awesome find in Fort Lee and Bergen County!
Would give 6 stars and more if possible!

Their food is actually really good! I saw their advertising, and thought I should stop by one day for Texas BBQ. Their brisket and burger with it is definitely something that none of any other local restaurants here offers. Will come back again and try other menus!

The quality of BBQ here is almost same as what you can taste in Texas. They didn't lower down the quality of flavor by replacing the selection of wood and way of cooking to something else. Their brisket looks amazing, and tastes fantastic!

Food was incredible, sat out back with covid going on and it was lovely. The staff was really friendly, definitely rooting for this place that just opened in February and had to shut down a month later! We got the brisket and it was some of the best brisket I’ve ever had and I’m pretty picky.
Awesome food and awesome staff! Would recommend without a doubt
Fabulous taste, very friendly staff, and excellent atmosphere that you will miss as soon as you leave the restaurant. Definitely 5 stars!
The food is regularly fresh and yummy, workers gives fantastic customer service. I love the cleanliness and vibes. Worth a try.

My family decided to try something new in this area, and ended up visiting this newly opened BBQ restaurant that sounded pretty good and interesting. We really loved the interior which is not often found especially in this area. We ordered burger menu and ribs. Including our kids, we loved it so much!
This Texas BBQ place is the legit one. I tried several menus here, and nothing was uncomfortable nor disappointing while I really love their brisket!
Had combo a. Plenty of food for 2 almost 3. Juicy ribs, briskets, pork belly, chicken. Much much better than expected!!!
Great food!  The atmosphere is nice and rustic too. Also plenty of parking. Would definitely come here again!
omg this food is SO BAD! yuck. NEVER EVER eating here again. My stomach hurt SO MUCH afterwards and I barely ate. YUCK never again.
I'm really glad that this unique BBQ restaurant entered into this town of Fort Lee which contributes to great diversity that I was loning for.

I love coleslaw, and love to compare one another. I love their coleslaw (and Mac & cheese), very mild and feels good. French fries look similar to others, still feels fresh and tastes good. Tried few main dishes, and all were above average. Overall, very fine restaurant~!
Loved their seafood boiling pot. I tried one with citrus garlic sauce, and didn't leave any tiny piece in the bowl. It was very delicious!

If you got tired of burgers from franchises such as McDonald, or high-end brands like Shake Shack, or even quality patty one from local restaurant, you should definitely visit this place. Their burgers are extra ordinary, sides are all fresh and not stimulating.
Their brisket burger is very outstanding..!! I see the other two burgers that look super yummy. I will definitely come back to try those out too!
I have been waiting for a long time for this place to re-open again. And now I Love what they (had to) brought to this area. I liked so much about the atmosphere and food selection they offer
Top notch quality Texas BBQ place! Heard they just did a soft opening. I can feel this this place will soon become a must-eat-place in this area.
Good BBQ and great atmosphere. A little over priced but it's the only decent BBQ with like 20+ miles
Amazing meat and great price! I usually don't come to this area often, but now came to have a very important reason to visit the town! Will definitely come back with a group~

Now officially my new favorite place to eat in town! I tried here before which I liked and last night was my second visit already. I had their special combo tray A to-go (I suppose it's their new menu on the list) and it was beyond satisfaction for the price you pay! Everything were so delicious, smoky and flavorful. I'd say their brisket is top-notch, but my hubby likes their spicy bacon the most.  I think this will be our new casual dine-in and take-out place whenever we get a craving for BBQ  Next time I'll try the seafood boiling pot! (Haven't tried yet, saw other's having it and the smell was irresistible!)

Like many others, I was sad for the closing of JD. But that wasn't an end...!! This newly renovated restaurant seems to be bringing something very hot to the town!! I can still see many same menus from JD, and they have more!! Their hickory-wood smoked brisket is one of my favorite now. I completely emptied out my plate!
Very attentiveM friendly, and helpful welcoming STILL even with self service! Foods are awesome with great look! Definitely worth a try!
It was our first visit here with my family. I must say that we all had very great experience from the beginning to the end. Their meats were very good, and everything is on point. Very satisfied.
Can't believe such a quality food and taste can be offered at this location and with such a reasonable price! They brought Manhattan quality and Texas taste into Fort Lee.
I love this restaurant sooooooooo much! I finally found a great place to hang out with non-Korean friends in Fort Lee~!! LOL
Tried beef rib and boiling pot with seafood. Taste was awesome!!
Great location and atmosphere, foods are even greater! New start of the restaurant, but seems already dominating the area!
Fantastic BBQ place in the heart of Fort Lee. Love the new vibe here. If you got bored of Korean foods in this area, check out this place.
Very nice place that gives great feeling as soon as entering the hall. Very competitive price and taste that you won't regret. Any of your guest will be satisfied!
It was their soft opening, but I fell in love with this place already! Will come again, again, again, and AGAIN~!!!
Had a very good meal with brisket burger and fries.
I was fascinated by their Brisket and Pulled Pork!
Excellent taste and outstanding quality of meats here! Tried all BBQ that they have, and no words can contain the fabulous experience that those brought!
Perfect price and taste, AND the vibe! Glad that they opened again with most of good things kept, and with additional great stuffs!
Best BBQ place in New Jersey! Their brisket and beef rib were good! You definitely should come and visit!
The whole experience at Oiso was fantastic! Every person who interacted with our table was very friendly. Every food that we ordered didn't disappoint us as all! Best place to hang out in New Jersey!

Food was good at a reasonable price.  Everything was self service and you pay 1st before you pick up the food. Don’t know why there was a tipping option when the waiters didn’t do anything except take your order.  Since it was a bbq restaurant, they should offer hand wipes with your meal.  Will go back as the food was good.
Great BBQ flavor.  Smokey and Woody we tried the baby back ribs, bacon and brisket.  All were delicious.  Order at counter and self seat.  Texas barn decor that they spent time you get good details.

First off, I worked at JDs before so I was pretty depressed when I heard they closed. Oiso has kept a lot of my favorite menu items which is a HUGE RELIEF. Changes I've noticed are all welcomed and keep with the spirit of JDs.  The mac and cheese is different but just as good in a smaller side size portion and smaller price. It's my favorite kind of mac and cheese with a perfect balance of cream and saltiness.  The pickled chayote is something that any foodie would appreciate. It's got a sweet, sour, salty balance I love in Filipino cuisine.  The brisket is the same: tender deliciousness. On the brisket sandwich, there's carmelized onions which IMO replace the need of a sauce.  There is Korean style fried chicken now as well. The soy garlic is heavier on the garlic.  I look forward to patronizing Oiso, in the best meaning of the term.  Bravo.

It’s a new place and I’ll have to give it to them the place looks pretty good considering.  Clean with that rustic look one would expect from a bbq spot.  I’ve only tried the ribs and I’d give it the thumbs up if you like the falling off the bone long flavorful smoked ribs.  The bar was well stocked and tap just needed a few more options (3’s not enough for some). All and all I excited to try the rest of the menu.

The atmosphere is awesome. The decor is very authentic. I know it's a soft opening. However, you do want to get the basics rights. The brisket is dry. They may want to choose a brisket with a bit more fat content.  They did a few things right. Their pulled pork and ribs were delicious with perfect smoke rings. And those pickles. Awesome.  The bar is stocked and provide options. But in reality you just want cold bottle beers. Fancy drinks really dont mix.  As a Texas native I understand the intentions. But they sorta missed the mark. Will revisit to see if things get better.
One of the Best BBQ places I ever visit. I had a Brisket and boiling pot with cornbread and it was amazing.

YOU SHOULD VISIT THIS AMAZING, NEW BBQ RESTAURANT! Food was soooooo GOOD! Their Baby back ribs were so tender, moist and juicy! Try their sides like cornbread(so amazing!), coleslaw, pickles, and salad!!! I'm pretty sure this restaurant will be a MUST-VISIT restaurant in Fort Lee!
